body_html: @bodokaiser yes, feed_dict is only needed for data external to TensorFlow. So doing feed_dict={x: batch[0].eval(session=session), is a bit odd, since you are taking data out of TF runtime, and putting it back-in without modification

body: @bodokaiser yes, `feed_dict` is only needed for data external to TensorFlow. So doing `feed_dict={x: batch[0].eval(session=session),` is a bit odd, since you are taking data out of TF runtime, and putting it back-in without modification
